                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13253209" author="jcoveney" created="Fri, 13 Apr 2012 08:58:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree, so here is a patch! I probably need to add more tests. Incidentally, I went ahead and used &quot;IsEmpty&quot; as my guinea pig, so this patch gives us &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2065&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2065&lt;/a&gt;. It took a bit to grok the relationship between POUserFunc and POForEach, but it doesn&apos;t touch that much code. Basically, it keeps track of all of the UDFs that have terminated early, and if they all terminate early, it terminates early.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13272757" author="jcoveney" created="Thu, 10 May 2012 21:58:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Tests are fun, so I added some! Given the code in question, e2e tests seemed most appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13272758" author="jcoveney" created="Thu, 10 May 2012 22:01:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Forgot to add apache headers. Added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13272761" author="jcoveney" created="Thu, 10 May 2012 22:08:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Added Javadocs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13272822" author="jcoveney" created="Thu, 10 May 2012 23:03:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Remove a line left from testing in IsEmpty&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13279098" author="alangates" created="Fri, 18 May 2012 20:14:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, lgtm&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13280376" author="jcoveney" created="Mon, 21 May 2012 20:08:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Awesome. Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
